postcontent:
These pistols are new. As a handgun, they are not subject to 922r rules, so they are not rebuilt by CAI, but come as originally assembled by Serbian famed Zastava factory.

They have 10.25" barrels, box, instruction manual, cleaning rod, and 2 BHO magazines. The total with tax is $470. They are new, and have warranty from Century.

My review of a very similar M85PV (same thing, except in 223) is here: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/M85.aspx

I have the last 5 which are coming Wednesday. If you want one, please make an appointment to pick up (see below) no earlier than 2/26). The distributor is now completely out, so this is it. LAST CHANCE!

FAQ

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to
www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the
appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site,
by making an appointment to buy. Someone could be doing it right now, and first person
to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy,
read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just
before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you
shortly.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy,
read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only
times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other
time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to
offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military
as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see
here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Forged upper and lower receivers are contoured to be more ergonomic. Compact design is both lightweight and only 1/2” longer than a 5.56 MSR receiver, 5/8” shorter than the current LR-308.

Lower receiver incorporates integral trigger guard and accepts any standard MSR pistol grip.

REDUCED WEIGHT, YET LIGHTER RECOIL

Reduced mass carrier provides smoother, softer recoil impulse than the GEN1 .308.

REDUCED MASS, FORGED, MONOLITHIC BOLT CARRIERWITH FORWARD ASSIST

New lightweight, forged, monolithic bolt carrier utilizes an integral gas key tower and removable gas key extension.

BEVELED MAG WELL

The beveled mag well provides a comfortable grip for those that prefer a mag well hold and also aids in quicker mag changes.

IMPROVED BOLT & BARREL EXTENSION

An all new bolt geometry provides superior lockup and strength. The bolt geometry allows a smaller diameter barrel extension to be used, in turn allowing upper receiver to be smaller, reducing overall material and weight without compromising strength.

IMPROVED EXTRACTOR & ELASTOMER EXTRACTOR SPRING

Through countless hours of research, testing, and tens of thousands of fired rounds, DPMS has selected a new extractor material that is nearly impervious to breaking, and a patent pending elastomer extractor spring. We ran tens of thousands of rounds through during testing without fatigue, breakage, failure, and the new materials resisted temperatures from -60˚F to 650˚F+ as well as every gun cleaner, solvent, oil or degreaser we could get our hands on.

DUAL EJECTORS

The dual ejector system reduces the ejector spring fatigue. Through duplicity, the likelihood of a failed ejection is significantly reduced.

STEEL FEED RAMP

GII incorporates an inserted steel feed ramp, allowing a lighter, smaller barrel extension and receiver, while improving feeding of more ammunition types.

ENLARGED EJECTION PORT

Lengthened port allows for better, more consistent ejection.

The Marlin 56 is a classic. It's a very unique rifle, this is one of the originals that has a steel receiver that has a serial number and a solid walnut stock. I believe only a few thousand were serial numbered because at the time it was not required and actually cost more to do. Later models were made out of aluminum and didn't last long. What's really nice about this rifle is it uses a cam and roller system so the lever only has a 25 degree throw, meaning you can fire and load the next round comfortably without losing sight on the target.
